"{\"uid\": \"rnz.co.nz-news-olympics-2024-524706-olympics-2024-egyptian-wrestler-arrested-in-paris-for-alleged-sexual-assault\", \"text\": \"Mohamed Elsayed, pictured at the Tokyo Olympics, is accused of sexually assaulting a cafe customer in Paris.Photo:AFP/JACK GUEZ  French police have arrested an Egyptian Olympic wrestler on suspicion of sexual assault outside a cafe he had visited in the French capital, the Paris prosecutor's office said.  The wrestler was arrested for allegedly touching the buttocks of another customer at the cafe, prosecutors said in a statement, adding that an investigation had been opened.  Police did not release the wrestler's name but an official in the Egyptian delegation confirmed the wrestler's identity as Mohamed Elsayed, who won bronze in the Tokyo Games but lost in Paris in early stages.  Egypt's Olympic Committee said Elsayed would face a disciplinary hearing.  If the allegations were confirmed to be true, he could face sanctions that could go as far as life exclusion from competition, the committee said in a statement.  Elsayed had been given permission to watch the final wrestling match for his weight category but then failed to return to the mission headquarters and turned off his phone, the statement said.  - Reuters  Copyright \\u00a92024,Radio New Zealand  There is more than one way to skin a cat, and tally medals. Let us pick the one that's best for us.  For more than 100 years, swimming in the river was banned due to health concerns. Now, Olympic athletes are competing in it and falling sick.  Filipino gymnast Carlos Yulo's fight with his mother has been making headlines in his home country, threatening to drown out the euphoria over his twin golds.  The Paris Olympics will close on Monday after 329 gold-medal events.  for ad-free news and current affairs  Olympics 2024 RSS  Follow RNZ News\"}"